subSubSection.paragraph:
REMARKS: This species has an antitropical distribution in the western Pacific. The northern and southern forms differ in their vertebral count, 135–143 and 129–135 respectively (
Smith and Böhlke 1997: 183
). If the southern form were recognized as a species, no name would be available for it.
